# CloudWatch Logs Insights — count FM API-integration errors by type (ThrottlingException &c).
#
# Run against /relay/bedrock/model-invocations. The runbook's diagnostic for "Throttling
# bursts" (skill 5.2.2): a spike of ThrottlingException rows means you are hitting a model
# quota — the remedy is the M3 exponential backoff + jitter (already in relay/llm.py) and/or a
# quota increase, NOT a code rewrite. Grouping by errorCode shows which integration error is
# spiking (throttling vs validation vs access-denied) so you diagnose the right one.

fields @timestamp, errorCode, modelId
| filter ispresent(errorCode)
| stats count(*) as occurrences by errorCode, modelId
| sort occurrences desc
